CatDescriptText: Partial article with image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 13, 1952, pg. 22, reads: "Chandu Back With Amazing Fire Feats - Chandu, the Magician - absent from the local scene for many months - stopped briefly in Pittsburgh last week on the first leg of a public relations tour through the East and Midwest preparatory to commencing a series of night club and theatre appearances. Nattily dressed in a smart gray flannel suit, topped off with a bright red fez bearing some mystic insignia, Chaundu paused briefly at the Courier's offices to say 'hello' to his friends...."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Chandu the magician wearing fez and breathing fire, in front of light colored background and dark parted curtains, in Harris Studio
